name: Lotus Esprit s1
description:
2048 x 3072 (2:3 ratio)

"Wet Nellie" is a Lotus Esprit s1 customized to be both a car and a submarine. Made for the 10th Bond Film "The spy who loved me" from 1977, starring Roger Moore, Barbara Bach and Curt Jürgens. In September 2013 the car was bought in an auction by Elon Musk to convert it into a functional car-submarine.
